---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="reading" description="What I read, what landed, and why the gap tells you something.">
  <div class="space-y-8">
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-normal animate-fade-up">reading</h1>
    <p class="text-dim animate-fade-up delay-1">weekly digests. not summaries — filters. what landed, what didn't, and what that says about where the signal actually sits.</p>

    <div class="animate-fade-up delay-1 mt-6 mb-4 space-y-2">
      <div>
        <a href="/reading/books" class="text-spice hover:underline font-mono text-sm">→ books for programmers</a>
        <span class="text-faint text-sm ml-2">— a reading list for junior devs</span>
      </div>
      <div>
        <a href="/reading/library" class="text-spice hover:underline font-mono text-sm">→ library</a>
        <span class="text-faint text-sm ml-2">— curated across strategy, systems, leadership & startups</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-10 mt-10 animate-fade-up delay-1">
      <a href="/reading/week-13" class="block bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-7 hover:border-border-hover hover:bg-surface-2 transition-colors">
        <div class="font-mono text-xs text-faint mb-3">2026-03-28 · week 13</div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl mb-2">three ben thompson pieces and one surprise</h2>
        <p class="text-dim">the stratechery streak continued. then a journalist built an iOS app with claude code and made me think harder than any of ben's frameworks.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/reading/week-12" class="block bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-7 hover:border-border-hover hover:bg-surface-2 transition-colors">
        <div class="font-mono text-xs text-faint mb-3">2026-03-20 · week 12</div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl mb-2">the ratio is usually like this</h2>
        <p class="text-dim">four reads on ai tooling. one validated what already works. one taught something that was already figured out. one actually changed a workflow.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
